2:T427,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"How to Manually Open an Electric Gate During a Power Cut","description":"Power cut in London? Learn exactly how to manually open your electric gate using the manual release key. Step-by-step emergency guide.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/how-to-manually-open-electric-gate/","datePublished":"2026-02-28","dateModified":"2026-02-28","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/images/gates/gate-swing-open-night-stone-pillars-drive.png","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/how-to-manually-open-electric-gate/"}}3:T631,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Where is the manual release on my electric gate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For ram-arm motors, the manual release is a key barrel or lever on the motor housing itself, usually covered by a small weatherproof cap. For underground motors, it is accessed via a cover plate on the top of the post cap. Your installer should have shown you the location and supplied the release key at handover."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What do I do if I have lost the manual release key?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Contact your gate installer or the motor manufacturer with your motor model details. Most manufacturers can supply replacement keys. A gate engineer can also supply and fit a replacement key barrel if the original is damaged."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will my electric gate work during a power cut?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"If a battery backup unit was installed, it will continue to power the motor for 20 to 50 cycles after mains power fails. After the battery is exhausted, or if no battery backup is fitted, the gate must be operated using the manual release."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"My manual release will not turn — what should I do?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Do not force it. Apply a penetrating lubricant to the barrel and allow it to work for five minutes before trying again. If it still will not turn, call a gate engineer — forcing a seized mechanism risks breaking the release entirely."}}]}6:["slug","how-to-manually-open-electric-gate","d"]
